fwb@netcom.com (fwb) writes:
> RSA's just crying over spilled milk...

This is true, pragmatically speaking, although they may be able to win damages 
in court if they find who actually spilled it.

> I for one cannot understand 
> how these greedy fucks were granted such a broad patent....  unless 
> it were expedient for the government to control the outlet of 
> such technologies. 

Of course it's expedient for the government to control the dispersal of 
cryptographic technologies.  But that's not the issue here--the issue is 
disclosure of a trade secret, which has nothing to do with patents whatsoever.

> Munitions export laws indeed.  This is all such crap.  How is it that 
> we can consider the "argument" of how secure cryptosystems 
> constitute "munitions" and should be kept out of the hands of citizens 
> to be even a lamb's hair above insane???! 

We don't.  Our distinguished representatives in Washongton, however, are 
another matter entirely.


